FBIS4-61864 "drsov091_b_94021" FBIS-SOV-94-091 Daily Report 11 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Go-Ahead Given for Sea-Based Space Launch Project Go-Ahead Given for Sea-Based Space Launch Project PM1105100394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 May 94 First Edition p 4 PM1105100394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Directive No. 624-r of the Russian Federation Government, signed by Russian Premier V. Chernomyrdin and dated 3 May 1994, Moscow] [Text] 1. The "Energiya" Science-and-Production Association named for Academician S.P. Korolev shall be authorized to create in accordance with prescribed procedure, jointly with foreign participants, an enterprise to develop [razrabotka] a sea-based space rocket for launching various space devices. 2. The "Energiya" Science-and-Production Association named for Academician S.P. Korolev shall be given responsibility for coordinating the work of Russian enterprises and cooperating with Ukrainian enterprises in the creation of the above space rocket complex. [Signed] V. Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Russian Federation Government. [Dated] Moscow, 3 May 1994.
